!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

academic /ˌækəˈdɛmɪk/

(academics) 

1. ADJ Academic is used to describe things that relate to the work done in schools, colleges, and universities, especially work that involves studying and reasoning rather than practical or technical skills. 学术上的 [ADJ n] 

例： Their academic standards are high. 他们的学术水平很高。 

2. academically ADV 学术上地 

例： He is academically gifted. 他在学术方面有天份。 

3. ADJ Academic is used to describe things that relate to schools, colleges, and universities. 学校的 [ADJ n] 

例： ...the start of the last academic year. …上一个学年的开始。 

4. ADJ Academic is used to describe work, or a school, college, or university, that places emphasis on studying and reasoning rather than on practical or technical skills. 学术的 

例： The author has settled for a more academic approach. 该作者已经确定了一种更学术的方法。 

5. ADJ Someone who is academic is good at studying. 学习好的 

例： The system is failing most disastrously among less academic children. 这种制度在学习不太好的学生中最失败。 

6. ADJ You can say that a discussion or situation is academic if you think it is not important because it has no real effect or cannot happen. 空谈的 

例： Who wants to hear about contracts and deadlines that are purely academic? 谁想听那些完全不切实际的合同和最后期限呢? 

7. N-COUNT An academic is a member of a university or college who teaches or does research. 学者 

例： A group of academics say they can predict house prices through a computer program. 一批学者声称，他们可以通过一种电脑程序预测房价。

</div>

